data.title: News
data.text: Officials cut ribbon, dedicate building to Marine Corps hero - From right: Col. James C. Carroll III, commanding officer, Marine Corps Logistics Base Albany; Maj. Gen. Craig C. Crenshaw, commanding general, Marine Corps Logistics Command; and Navy Lt. Cmdr. Jason Boatright, public works officer, MCLB Albany, cut a ribbon for the new $14.5 million Weapons Storage and Inspection Facility, here, Aug. 24. The building was dedicated in memory of Medal of Honor recipient Chief Warrant Officer 4 Harold E. Wilson, who was also the adjutant here for then-Headquarters Battalion, Supply Center Marine Corps Base Albany, in the 1960s.
